Monster Slots
by: Ray Miller
kaynekayne@bigfoot.com

Place the lever then in the vacinity of the lever place the three custom waypoints reel1, reel2, and reel3.  Place them in order from left to right.

If you want to create more than one slot machine change this lever's tag and give the waypoints a tag of "REEL#_<tag of lever> to designate the lever to which they respond.

This is the spawn point for the Reel 1 symbol of a "Monster Slots" slot machine by Ray Miller.

Give it a tag to correspond with the lever to which it belongs.  i.e. "REEL1_<tag of lever>"

This is the spawn point for the Reel 2 symbol of a "Monster Slots" slot machine by Ray Miller.

Give it a tag to correspond with the lever to which it belongs.  i.e. "REEL2_<tag of lever>"

This is the spawn point for the Reel 3 symbol of a "Monster Slots" slot machine by Ray Miller.

Give it a tag to correspond with the lever to which it belongs.  i.e. "REEL3_<tag of lever>"

This is the default waypoint you may place to set a patrol path for a creature or NPC.
1. Create the creature and either use its current Tag or fill in a new one.
2. Place or make sure the WalkWayPoints() is within the body of the On Spawn script for the creature.
3. Place a series of waypoints along the route you wish the creature to walk.
4. Select all of the newly created waypoints and right click. Choose the Create Set option.
5. The waypoint set will have a set name of "WP_" + NPC Tag. Thus if an NPC with the Tag "Guard" will have a waypoint set called "WP_Guard". Note that Tags are case sensitive.
